About the naming of cpuArray vs. nodeArray: The term "cpu" is used in many places in the code and it is fairly consistent and unambiguous. The term "node" is used too, but it is very ambiguous and in most cases it means something very different than what we think of today (NSK nodes). So, I try to stay away from the term "node" (except in comments, where I usually say "Linux node").

Looks good. You can consider to remove setting the rootLogger in both wdt and psd to keep it in sync with the rest of the config files of Trafodion. Also, set the immediateFlush=true to ensure that the logs are written.  I think Wdt and Psd logs are kept to a minimum and hence it shouldn't affect the performance

Not sure what you mean by removing the rootLogger in wdt and psd as all other config files are set the same way?

Zalo

Remove these lines in the config file
 \# Define the root logger to the system property "trafodion.root.logger".
 trafodion.root.logger=INFO, psdAppender		 trafodion.root.logger=INFO, psdAppender
 log4j.rootLogger=${trafodion.root.logger}		 log4j.rootLogger=${trafodion.root.logger}

and modify the line as
log4j.logger.WDG=INFO,psdAppender

And add
log4j.appender.psdAppender.immediateFlush=true

Need to do the similar changes with wdt config file too
